<br>
Has any one besides me noticed that the old world quests really suck?<br>
<br>
Let me give you this fun instance...<br>
<br>
As a friend of mine named Zorendil recently dinged 50, I thought I'd do him a favor for all the times he's helped me by helping him do his level 50 ranger quest spell...<br>
<br>
Just to complete one fourth of the quest, we had to spend over 20 hours camping in Mistmoore.<br>
<br>
The Butler in Mistmoore's rare drop is a Fang.  The butler is a rare spawn.  The Maid in Mistmoore's rare drop is a Fang.  The maid is a rare spawn.  The quest NPC to turn the fangs into to get the piece for the spell, the avenging caitliff, is also a rarespawn in mistmoore (and occasionally camped because he drops nice loot.)  Then we had to kill the reanimated hand in LGuk and some imps in SolB.<br>
<br>
This seems to be to be a little over the top for a level 49 spell that is preempted by later spells.  In the same amount of time it took me, Zorendil, and sometimes our friend Kassara to get this spell, me and Zor could have leveled, which would have increased our abilities much more than a 200point fire dd.  Is the power this spell provides really overbalancing enough to cause it to only come into the game at best once every 3 days at best?<br>
<br>
This isn't the only sucky quest though.  The SK level 50 spell is expensive and annoying to obtain, and is also preempted by a later spell.<br>
<br>
The newbie old world quests kinda suck too.  Why would somebody play a human bard of Qeynos for the quests compared to say, a Vah Shir bard of Shar Vahl's quests?  The only two quests available to Qeynos bards at low level is the mail quest, and another courier quest that gets you the level 6 song (which is easily buyable.)  Freeport is similar.<br>
<br>
Why do I bring this up you ask?  I dunno, just pestered me how much some of the quests suck on the old world as far as risk+time vs. reward.<br>
<br>
Sincerely, <p><FONT SIZE=1>
